comments.content:
OK so after looking at the Github code i think it is in fact AC after all:
"virtualNetworkPeerings": [
 {
 "name": "spoke1-hub-peer",
 "allowForwardedTraffic": true,
 "allowGatewayTransit": false,
 "useRemoteGateways": true,
 "remoteVirtualNetwork": {
 "resourceGroupName": "hub-vnet-rg",
 "name": "hub-vnet"
 }
 }

Notice that the spoke configuration uses the "allowForwardedTraffic" option, as well as "useRemoteGateways".
